findScreens

protected java.util.List<org.ontoware.rdf2go.model.node.URI> findScreens(java.util.List<Screen> screens,
                                                                         java.util.List<Condition> preconditions,
                                                                         java.util.List<Condition> postconditions,
                                                                         boolean plugin,
                                                                         boolean subsume,
                                                                         int offset,
                                                                         int limit,
                                                                         java.util.List<java.lang.String> tags,
                                                                         org.ontoware.rdf2go.model.node.URI predicate)
                                                                  throws org.ontoware.rdf2go.exception.ModelRuntimeException
Search for screens inside the catalogue which satisfy the unsatisfied preconditions of a list of screens and also takes into account the domain context composed by a list of tags. If within the list of screens there are not unsatisfied preconditions, no screens will be returned because it is assume that there is no need to satisfied any condition. If any tag is given, the list of screens to be returned will be filtered by this tag. If no tag is given, no tag filter will be done. If the number of screens returned is high, you can use the parameters OFFSET and LIMIT in order to retrieve small lists of screens.

Parameters:
screens - list of screens (must be a list of 'clones')
plugin - ignored at this version
subsume - ignored at this version
offset - indicate the start of the list of screens to be returned
limit - specify the maximum number of screens to be returned [negative means no limit]
tags - a list of tags for filtering the results
Returns:
a recommended list of screens according to the input given
Throws:
java.lang.ClassCastException
org.ontoware.rdf2go.exception.ModelRuntimeException

getUnsatisfiedConditions

protected java.util.ArrayList<Condition> getUnsatisfiedConditions(java.util.List<Screen> screenList,
                                                                  java.util.List<Condition> preconditions,
                                                                  java.util.List<Condition> postconditions,
                                                                  boolean plugin,
                                                                  boolean subsume)
Retrieves all the unsatisfied preconditions of a list of screens. It also checks whether a 'postcondition' is satisfied. NOTE: 'preconditions' are always satisfied

Parameters:
screenList - A list of screens (to extract their pre/postconditions)
preconditions - A list of preconditions
postconditions - A list of postconditions
plugin - ignored at this version
subsume - ignored at this version
Returns:

isConditionSatisfied

public boolean isConditionSatisfied(java.util.List<Condition> conditionList,
                                    java.util.List<Screen> screenList,
                                    Condition conditionToCheck,
                                    boolean plugin,
                                    boolean subsume,
                                    org.ontoware.rdf2go.model.node.URI screenExcluded)
Determines if a specific precondition is satisfied by a list of screens, in other words, check if any postcondition of the list of screens satisfy the precondition. Usually the list of screens will include the screen which the precondition belongs to, hence you can set if a screen has to be excluded while checking.

Parameters:
screenList - a list of screens which might satisfy the precondition
conditionToCheck - the condition to check if it is satisfied
plugin - not yet implemented
subsume - not yet implemented
screenExcluded - the URI of the screen which will be ignored while checking
Returns:
true if the condition is satisfied

importMissingOntologies

protected void importMissingOntologies(org.ontoware.rdf2go.model.Model model)
Imports into the catalogue any ontology which is being used in the given model, in the form of a concept or a property for example. Ex: if the model contains the URI http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Person, the FOAF (http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1) ontology will be imported.

Parameters:
model - set of triples used to check for URIs
